~ Rachel

0GJ6oKGrG0I.title: Roggen- Apfelmus Buns [Deutsches Grill- BBQ & Backrezept]
0GJ6oKGrG0I.description:
Heute gibt es ein paar wunderbar fluffige Roggen – Apfelmus Buns. Diese passen perfekt zu kräftigem Fleisch wie Wild oder geräuchertes Rindfleisch, auch zu Brisket passen diese Buns sehr gut! Vor allem sind diese Buns wirklich ganz einfach selbst herzustellen, alles was Ihr dafür benötigt ist:

200g 550 Weizenmehl
300g 1150 dunkles Roggenmehl

200ml Milch
1 Ei
50g Butter

1 Riegel Hefe (40 Gramm)
3El Apfelmus

Salz

Die Milch müsst Ihr zusammen mit der Butter etwas erhitzen bis sie lauwarm, bzw. die Butter geschmolzen ist. In der Zwischenzeit schon einmal das Mehl in eine Schüssel geben und vermischen. Nun eine Kuhle in die Mitte drücken und die Hefe hineinbröseln. 

Als nächstes gießt Ihr Euer lauwarmes Butter – Milch Gemisch über die Hefe und knetet mit einer Küchenmaschine mit Knethaken in der Mitte einen kleinen Vorteig (bitte NUR das Milch Butter Gemisch mit der Hefe und etwas Mehl verkneten, NICHT die kompletten Zutaten miteinander vermengen).  Wenn alles miteinander vermengt ist, bedeckt Ihr die Schüssel mit einem Küchentuch und lasst den Vorteig 10 Minuten gehen. 

Nach 10 Minuten sollte Euer Vorteig Blasen werfen, nun gebt Ihr ein Ei, eine gute Prise Salz und das Apfelmus dazu. Als nächstes wird dann der komplette Teig miteinander vermengt bis ein ordentlicher Teigklumpen entstanden ist. Diesen bedeckt Ihr wieder mit einem Tuch und lasst ihn 25 Minuten gehen. 

Zum Abschluss knetet Ihr den Teig nochmal ordentlich durch und formt dann 12 kleine Kugeln daraus. Diese gebt Ihr auf ein mit Backpapier ausgelegtes Blech und lasst sie nochmal 10 Minuten ruhen. Nun drückt Ihr sie leicht an und gebt sie bei 200 Grad Ober- und Unterhitze in den Backofen. Unter Euer Backblech solltet Ihr eine feuerfeste Schüssel mit warmem Wasser stellen. Nach 20-25 Minuten sollten Eure Buns fertig sein! 

Guten Appetit!

Dsz4zNtHQ9k.title: Moonlight Sonata Classical Guitar Eric Henderson
Dsz4zNtHQ9k.description:
Eric Henderson (https://www.erichendersonguitar.com) - Download this song from here https://www.erichendersonguitar.com/store/moonlight-sonata-by-l-von-beethoven

Visit Eric online and join the mailing list for the latest in news and updates. https://www.erichendersonguitar.com/join/

Want free Classical Guitar Lessons from Eric? Visit https://www.erichendersonguitar.com/store/free-classical-guitar-lessons-eric-henderson

Classical Guitar - Moonlight Sonata Eric Henderson is one of only three people to study privately with the master guitarist Andres Segovia.

Eric Henderson spent several years in Spain learning the intricacies of the classical guitar, while playing as much as 12 hours a day. In addition to studying with Andres Segovia, Henderson has studied guitar with Christopher Parkening, Angel Romero, Ernesto Bitetti, Emilio Pujol and Antonia Morales. He has spent time studying Baroque interpretation with Ton Koopman and Henk Dekker, and theory and composition with Aureo Hererro. While Eric was in Spain he also had the honor of studying with the great composer Federico Moreno Torroba, perfecting the interpretation of Torrobas Sonatina in A.

Eric Henderson's new CD "Homage" and DVD "Homage Guitar Masterpieces" are a collection of pieces he has studied, arranged and performed over the last four decades. Both the CD and DVD include pieces by Bach, Villa Lobos, and other standards of the classical guitar. Eric also performs his arrangements of Little Wing by Jimi Hendrix and the Jagger/Richards song, Paint it Black as well three original compositions.

Ludwig van Beethoven, is popularly known for his "Moonlight" Sonata . The work was completed in 1801 and rumored to be dedicated to his pupil, Countess Giulietta Guicciardi. The name "Moonlight" Sonata derives from an 1832 description of the first movement by music critic Ludwig Rellstab, who compared it to moonlight shining upon Lake Lucerne which is in central Switzerland.

5VK6j9RwXBo.title: Divinity 2: Ego Draconis Gameplay
5VK6j9RwXBo.description:
I thought I'd show some gameplay on the Divinity 2 game. The game itself is an action-oriented RPG that lets you control an up and coming Dragon Slayer. In this game, dragons are the supposed evil baddies that eat human flesh and drink the blood of a thousand piglets-- Or so says a book I read in-game. Without revealing too much, the dragons are a soon-to-be extinct race that has safeguarded the humans for generations but was suddenly the target of human loathing. The basis for which the dragons were reverred -- the Dragon Knights, humans who were given the power of a Dragon were slain until to this day only one survived. And thats where you come in. You are a dragon slayer. 

Gameplay isn't too bad. 3.5 out of 5 pandas.
Music isn't really memorable but some suits the ambience of their environment than the rest.
The game doesn't pick up until about 3-6 hours into the game. Which would actually be a turn-off for some.  You see in this game, you start out ridiculously like a half-wit on crack. I mean, you cant even kill a goblin mage outside training camp without dying on hard level. Only later in the game do you appreciate your dragoney-ness. Still. The game needs a lot of improvement in terms of animation. I mean if you like bows? Don't use them. You look silly shooting them. Voice acting is not really bad. Not good either. Still there are occasional good voice overs. The best one is that sexy provacative voice that belonged to a treasure chest begging me to open her and take her treasures. Yes, there is one in the game. It was the hawtest experience I have had in 2009. 

The world, well... the world is kinda empty. In the beginning you kinda think  everything is alright but as you progress, you meet less people and then more annoying ones. 

The good thing about this game is the mind-reading capabilities of a dragon-slayer. In certain conversations, you can read the minds that would reveal certain information that you can use. Whether its a hidden cache of loot, passwords, or things you can use as threats.

OMG YOU KEELZ DRAGUNZ FO FUNNIEZ!
